    when: '2026-04-21',
    title: 'HMAC unsubscribe tokens',
    items: [
      'workers/sparrow-digest/src/signing.ts · Web Crypto HMAC-SHA256 · signUnsubToken / verifyUnsubToken / buildUnsubUrl',
      'Token shape: <urlencoded-email>.<unix-seconds-expiry>.<lowercase-hex-hmac> · 30-day TTL',
      'Constant-time HMAC compare so a timing oracle can\'t leak the correct prefix',
      'DELETE /api/sparrow/digest-subscribe now verifies: 400 on malformed/bad-hmac/missing-secret, 410 on expired, 200 on verify + KV delete',
      'Token accepted via x-unsub-token header OR ?unsub_token query param — email-footer links work from any browser without custom headers',
      'Worker renderDigestEmail is now async and wires buildUnsubUrl into the footer — text + HTML both',
      'SPARROW_DIGEST_SIGNING_KEY env binding required on BOTH the cron worker AND the Pages Function; rotating invalidates outstanding tokens',
      'Verify helper inlined in the Pages Function (Pages and Workers are separate deploy targets) — byte-identical to the canonical copy in signing.ts',
      'Cron dispatch + signals aggregation + Nostr client port + native NIP-01 profile lookup still pending — v0.35',
    ],
  },
  {
    v: 'v0.35',
    status: 'shipped',
    when: '2026-04-21',
    title: 'Nostr TS port · MailChannels retry · friends-saved email summary',
    items: [
      'workers/sparrow-digest/src/nostr.ts · TypeScript port of NostrRelayClient.swift · Web WebSocket + JSON frames · collectFromRelay + collectAcrossRelays + newestPerAuthorByDTag helpers',
      'Per-relay timeout 6s, 500-event safety cap, defensive re-filter by author (relays may echo spam), dedup by event.id across relays',
      'workers/sparrow-digest/src/send.ts · MailChannels extracted with retry-with-jitter · 3 attempts max · exponential ceilings 800ms / 1600ms / 3200ms with full jitter · 5xx/429/408 retriable · 401/403/422 fail-fast',
      'Retriable failures leave last_sent_at untouched so the next cron tick cleanly retries · permanent failures surface in the run log but also don\'t touch last_sent_at (ops sees them + can redeploy)',
      'renderDigestEmail v0.35 · subscribers with npub + relays get a live fetched "N of M followed signers published public saved lists · K total saved-block references" summary in both text and HTML',
      'Subscribers without npub still get the short "open signals" prompt — no regression for early signups',
      'Cron email signed-unsubscribe URL (v0.34) stitches cleanly with the new content',
      'Full signals aggregation mirror (co-saves + channel distribution) + block-lookup KV prefetch + dead-letter bucket queued for v0.36',
    ],
  },
  {
    v: 'v0.36',
    status: 'shipped',
    when: '2026-04-21',
    title: 'Full signals aggregation in the digest',
    items: [
      'workers/sparrow-digest/src/aggregate.ts · pure-function port of /sparrow/signals Panels 1 + 3',
      'aggregate(newestPerAuthor, lookup) → { activeFriends, totalSaves, topCoSaved[≥2], channelDist }',
      'First-picker attribution: earliest created_at among savers wins the ⭐ chip (mirrors /sparrow/signals)',
      'Email body carries HTML table of co-saved blocks (×N badge · № id · title · channel chip) + progress-bar channel breakdown + plain-text mirrors',
      'Block-lookup prefetch: /blocks.json fetched ONCE per cron tick with cf.cacheTtl:300 and passed to every subscriber\'s renderDigestEmail',
      'Beats 300+ /b/<id>.json requests per subscriber · returns {} on fetch failure · email still sends with "unknown block" rows',
      'Aggregation gated on ≥2 active friends · <2 still gets the v0.35 summary line · no-npub subscribers still get the v0.30 prompt',
      'Dead-letter bucket + native NIP-01 profile lookup queued for v0.37',
    ],
  },
  {
    v: 'v0.37',
    status: 'next',
    when: 'planned',
    title: 'Dead-letter bucket + native NIP-01 profile lookup',
    items: [
      'KV dead-letter bucket for repeated retriable failures · ops/dead-letter endpoint for human review',
      'Permanent-failure surfacing: subscriptions that hit the same non-retriable error 3 cron ticks in a row get flagged',
      'Native Sparrow.app gains NIP-01 kind-0 profile lookup so aliases auto-populate without going through the web',
      '/sparrow/digest preview page so subscribers can see the email they\'ll get before confirming frequency',
    ],
  },
  {
    v: 'v1.0',
    status: 'north star',
    title: 'The reader the broadcast deserves',
    items: [
      'Full offline archive (300+ blocks) in Service Worker + IndexedDB',
      'Cross-client read state via Nostr kind 30023 addressable events',
      'Agent-mode view served from /sparrow/llms.txt for machine readers',
      'Federated reading lists — subscribe to a friend\'s list as a feed',
    ],
  },
];

const stats = {
  channels: CHANNEL_LIST.length,
  kbShortcuts: 17, // + F friends jump (v0.24)
  routes: 10, // + /sparrow/signals (v0.28)
  cssTokens: 22,
};
---

<SparrowLayout
  title="About — what Sparrow is"
  description="Overview of Sparrow — features shipped in v0.2 and the path from here to v1.0."
  canonicalPath="/sparrow/about"
  homeHref="/sparrow"
>
  <section class="sp-about-hero">
    <span class="sp-kicker">✦ about · sparrow</span>
    <h1 class="sp-about-title">
      A reader for the<br />
      <em>living broadcast.</em>
    </h1>
    <p class="sp-about-dek">
      Sparrow is a hosted, keyboard-first client for
      <a class="sp-link" href="/">PointCast</a> — El Segundo's ongoing broadcast
      of blocks across {stats.channels} channels. It pairs with
      <a class="sp-link" href="/magpie">Magpie</a>, the local-first publisher
      Mike uses to push clips into the PointCast graph and its syndication
      pool (Mastodon · Farcaster · bitchat · Zora · Objkt · more).
    </p>

    <ul class="sp-stats">
      <li><strong>{stats.channels}</strong><span>channels</span></li>
      <li><strong>{stats.kbShortcuts}</strong><span>keyboard<br/>shortcuts</span></li>
      <li><strong>{stats.routes}</strong><span>routes shipping</span></li>
      <li><strong>OKLCH</strong><span>color space</span></li>
      <li><strong>0 kB</strong><span>framework<br/>runtime</span></li>
    </ul>

    <button type="button" class="sp-install-cta" data-sp-install-cta hidden>
      <span class="sp-install-cta-icon">↓</span>
      <span class="sp-install-cta-label">Install Sparrow as an app</span>
      <span class="sp-install-cta-hint">runs offline · appears when your browser offers it</span>
    </button>

    <a class="sp-memo-cta" href="/sparrow/deck">
      <span class="sp-memo-cta-stamp">TM</span>
      <span class="sp-memo-cta-body">
        <span class="sp-memo-cta-title">Read the Technical Memorandum</span>
        <span class="sp-memo-cta-hint">v0.4 · SPA-TM-26-0421 · a Bell Labs / Xerox PARC-style overview of Sparrow</span>
      </span>
      <span class="sp-memo-cta-arrow">→</span>
    </a>

    <a class="sp-native-cta" href="/sparrow/connect">
      <span class="sp-native-cta-glyph" aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
      <span class="sp-native-cta-body">
        <span class="sp-native-cta-title">Get the native menu-bar companion</span>
        <span class="sp-native-cta-hint">v0.6 · macOS 13+ · a small ✦ that pulses when new blocks land</span>
      </span>
      <span class="sp-native-cta-arrow">→</span>
    </a>
  </section>

  <section class="sp-about-section">
    <header class="sp-reel-head">
      <span class="sp-kicker">✦ v0.36 · what's in the build</span>
    </header>
    <ul class="sp-about-features">
      {features.map((f) => (
        <li class="sp-feature">
          <span class="sp-feature-kbd">{f.kbd}</span>
          <div class="sp-feature-text">
            <span class="sp-kicker" style="color: var(--sp-mute);">{f.kicker}</span>
            <h3 class="sp-feature-title">{f.title}</h3>
            <p class="sp-feature-body">{f.body}</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="sp-about-section">
    <header class="sp-reel-head">
      <span class="sp-kicker">✦ roadmap · v0.1 → v1.0</span>
    </header>
    <ol class="sp-roadmap">
      {roadmap.map((r) => (
        <li class={`sp-rm sp-rm--${r.status}`}>
          <header class="sp-rm-head">
            <span class="sp-rm-v">{r.v}</span>
            <span class={`sp-rm-status sp-rm-status--${r.status}`}>{r.status}</span>
            {r.when && <span class="sp-rm-when">{r.when}</span>}
          </header>
          <h3 class="sp-rm-title">{r.title}</h3>
          <ul class="sp-rm-items">
            {r.items.map((it) => <li>{it}</li>)}
          </ul>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="sp-about-section">
    <header class="sp-reel-head">
      <span class="sp-kicker">✦ design system · quick reference</span>
    </header>
    <div class="sp-design-grid">
      <article class="sp-design-card">
        <h3>palette</h3>
        <p class="sp-aside-mono">OKLCH, theme-aware via <code>color-mix()</code></p>
        <div class="sp-swatches">
          <span style="--s: var(--sp-ink);">ink</span>
          <span style="--s: var(--sp-blue-hour);">blue-hour</span>
          <span style="--s: var(--sp-bone);">bone</span>
          <span style="--s: var(--sp-ember);">ember</span>
          <span style="--s: var(--sp-moss);">moss</span>
          <span style="--s: var(--sp-oxblood);">oxblood</span>
          <span style="--s: var(--sp-lilac);">lilac</span>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="sp-design-card">
        <h3>channels</h3>
        <p class="sp-aside-mono">one OKLCH token per channel, computed from pointcast brand hexes</p>
        <div class="sp-swatches">
          {CHANNEL_LIST.map((c) => (
            <span style={`--s: var(--ch-${c.code.toLowerCase()});`}>{c.code}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="sp-design-card">
        <h3>typography</h3>
        <p class="sp-typespec"><span class="sp-typelabel">display</span><strong style="font-family: var(--sp-display);">Gloock</strong></p>
        <p class="sp-typespec"><span class="sp-typelabel">ui</span><strong style="font-family: var(--sp-ui); letter-spacing: -0.01em;">Inter Tight</strong></p>
        <p class="sp-typespec"><span class="sp-typelabel">mono</span><strong style="font-family: var(--sp-mono);">Departure Mono</strong></p>
      </article>
      <article class="sp-design-card">
        <h3>motion</h3>
        <p class="sp-aside-mono">all animations respect <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code></p>
        <ul class="sp-motion-list">
          <li>needle sweep (12s linear infinite)</li>
          <li>beacon radar sweep (6s)</li>
          <li>receiving pill pulse (2.4s)</li>
          <li>tuning progress bar (scroll-driven)</li>
          <li>reel → reader view-transition morph</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <aside class="sp-beacon">
    <span class="sp-beacon-sweep" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    <span class="sp-beacon-kicker">✦ sibling projects</span>
    <span class="sp-beacon-body">
      <a class="sp-link" href="/">pointcast</a> is the broadcast ·
      <a class="sp-link" href="/magpie">magpie</a> is the publisher ·
      sparrow is the reader
    </span>
    <a href="/sparrow" class="sp-link sp-beacon-cta">back to reel →</a>
  </aside>

  <style>
    .sp-about-hero {
      padding: 28px 0 36px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sp-rule);
    }
    .sp-about-title {
      font-family: var(--sp-display);
      font-weight: 400;
      font-size: clamp(40px, 6.5vw, 80px);
      line-height: 1.02;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      color: var(--sp-bone);
      margin: 12px 0 16px;
    }
    .sp-about-title em { font-style: italic; color: var(--sp-ember); }
    .sp-about-dek {
      font-size: 17px;
      color: var(--sp-ash);
      max-width: 64ch;
      margin: 0 0 24px;
    }
    .sp-stats {
      list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr));
      gap: 16px;
    }
    .sp-stats li {
      border: 1px solid var(--sp-rule);
      border-radius: var(--sp-rad);
      padding: 14px 16px;
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-blue-hour) 70%, transparent);
    }
    .sp-stats strong {
      display: block;
      font-family: var(--sp-display);
      font-weight: 400;
      font-size: 32px;
      line-height: 1;
      color: var(--sp-ember);
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .sp-stats span {
      display: block;
      margin-top: 6px;
      font-family: var(--sp-mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--sp-mute);
    }

    .sp-install-cta {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
      grid-template-areas: "icon label" "icon hint";
      gap: 2px 14px;
      align-items: center;
      margin-top: 24px;
      padding: 14px 20px;
      border: 1px solid var(--sp-ember);
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-ember) 12%, transparent);
      color: var(--sp-bone);
      border-radius: var(--sp-rad);
      cursor: pointer;
      text-align: left;
      transition: background 180ms ease, transform 180ms ease;
    }
    .sp-install-cta:hover {
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-ember) 22%, transparent);
      transform: translateY(-1px);
    }
    .sp-install-cta[hidden] { display: none; }
    .sp-install-cta-icon {
      grid-area: icon;
      font-family: var(--sp-display);
      font-size: 32px; line-height: 1;
      color: var(--sp-ember);
    }
    .sp-install-cta-label {
      grid-area: label;
      font-family: var(--sp-display);
      font-size: 18px;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .sp-install-cta-hint {
      grid-area: hint;
      font-family: var(--sp-mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--sp-mute);
    }

    /* Memo CTA — Bell Labs styling inside Sparrow's chrome. Stands out
       from the install button: bone paper card, oxblood rubber-stamp
       TM chip. Intentionally anachronistic next to the blue-hour HUD
       to telegraph "this is a different kind of artifact." */
    .sp-memo-cta {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;
      gap: 16px;
      align-items: center;
      margin-top: 14px;
      padding: 14px 18px;
      background: #f4efe2;
      color: #1a1612;
      border-radius: var(--sp-rad);
      border: 1px solid #9a8f78;
      box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-ink) 70%, transparent);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
      transition: transform 180ms ease, box-shadow 180ms ease;
    }
    .sp-memo-cta:hover {
      transform: translate(-2px, -2px);
      box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-ink) 70%, transparent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .sp-memo-cta-stamp {
      display: grid; place-items: center;
      width: 44px; height: 44px;
      border: 2px solid #7a1f1f;
      color: #7a1f1f;
      font-family: 'Space Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      transform: rotate(-3deg);
    }
    .sp-memo-cta-body { display: block; }
    .sp-memo-cta-title {
      display: block;
      font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 20px;
      line-height: 1.1;
      color: #1a1612;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .sp-memo-cta-hint {
      display: block;
      margin-top: 4px;
      font-family: 'Courier Prime', ui-monospace, monospace;
      font-size: 11px;
      color: #6a6255;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    }
    .sp-memo-cta-arrow {
      font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 26px;
      color: #7a1f1f;
    }

    /* Native-app CTA — sits directly below the memo CTA, uses the
       Sparrow blue-hour palette (not Bell Labs cream) so the two
       artifacts stay visually distinct side-by-side. */
    .sp-native-cta {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;
      gap: 16px;
      align-items: center;
      margin-top: 12px;
      padding: 14px 18px;
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-blue-hour) 90%, var(--sp-ember));
      color: var(--sp-bone);
      border-radius: var(--sp-rad);
      border: 1px solid var(--sp-ember);
      text-decoration: none;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-ember) 18%, transparent);
      transition: transform 180ms ease, box-shadow 180ms ease, background 180ms ease;
    }
    .sp-native-cta:hover {
      transform: translateY(-1px);
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-blue-hour) 78%, var(--sp-ember));
      box-shadow: 0 16px 40px color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-ember) 28%, transparent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .sp-native-cta-glyph {
      display: grid; place-items: center;
      width: 44px; height: 44px;
      border: 1px solid var(--sp-ember);
      border-radius: 50%;
      font-family: var(--sp-display);
      font-size: 20px;
      color: var(--sp-ember);
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-ember) 14%, transparent);
    }
    .sp-native-cta-body { display: block; }
    .sp-native-cta-title {
      display: block;
      font-family: var(--sp-display);
      font-size: 20px;
      color: var(--sp-bone);
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      line-height: 1.1;
    }
    .sp-native-cta-hint {
      display: block;
      margin-top: 4px;
      font-family: var(--sp-mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--sp-mute);
    }
    .sp-native-cta-arrow {
      font-family: var(--sp-display);
      font-size: 26px;
      color: var(--sp-ember);
    }

    .sp-about-section { padding: 36px 0 28px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sp-rule); }

    .sp-about-features {
      list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
      gap: 14px;
    }
    .sp-feature {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 72px 1fr;
      gap: 14px;
      padding: 16px 18px;
      border: 1px solid var(--sp-rule);
      border-radius: var(--sp-rad);
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-blue-hour) 80%, transparent);
    }
    .sp-feature-kbd {
      font-family: var(--sp-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 6px 8px;
      border: 1px solid var(--sp-ember);
      color: var(--sp-ember);
      border-radius: 3px;
      align-self: start;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .sp-feature-title { font-family: var(--sp-display); font-weight: 400; font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.1; color: var(--sp-bone); margin: 4px 0 6px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
    .sp-feature-body { font-size: 13.5px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--sp-ash); margin: 0; }

    .sp-roadmap { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: grid; gap: 18px; }
    .sp-rm {
      position: relative;
      border: 1px solid var(--sp-rule);
      border-radius: var(--sp-rad);
      padding: 18px 20px;
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-blue-hour) 75%, transparent);
    }
    .sp-rm--shipped { box-shadow: inset 4px 0 0 var(--sp-moss); }
    .sp-rm--next    { box-shadow: inset 4px 0 0 var(--sp-ember); border-color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-ember) 35%, var(--sp-rule)); }
    .sp-rm--planned { box-shadow: inset 4px 0 0 var(--sp-mute); opacity: 0.88; }
    .sp-rm--north.star,
    .sp-rm[class*="north"] { box-shadow: inset 4px 0 0 var(--sp-lilac); border-style: dashed; border-color: var(--sp-lilac); }
    .sp-rm-head { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .sp-rm-v {
      font-family: var(--sp-display);
      font-size: 28px;
      color: var(--sp-bone);
      letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    }
    .sp-rm-status {
      font-family: var(--sp-mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 3px 9px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid currentColor;
    }
    .sp-rm-status--shipped   { color: var(--sp-moss); }
    .sp-rm-status--next      { color: var(--sp-ember); background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-ember) 15%, transparent); }
    .sp-rm-status--planned   { color: var(--sp-mute); }
    .sp-rm-status--north.star,
    .sp-rm-status[class*="north"] { color: var(--sp-lilac); }
    .sp-rm-when { font-family: var(--sp-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--sp-mute); margin-left: auto; }
    .sp-rm-title { font-family: var(--sp-display); font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px; color: var(--sp-bone); margin: 0 0 10px; }
    .sp-rm-items { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: grid; gap: 5px; }
    .sp-rm-items li {
      padding-left: 18px;
      position: relative;
      font-size: 13.5px;
      color: var(--sp-ash);
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .sp-rm-items li::before {
      content: "◂"; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0;
      color: var(--sp-ember);
    }

    .sp-design-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
      gap: 14px;
    }
    .sp-design-card {
      border: 1px solid var(--sp-rule);
      border-radius: var(--sp-rad);
      padding: 16px 18px;
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--sp-blue-hour) 78%, transparent);
    }
    .sp-design-card h3 {
      font-family: var(--sp-mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--sp-ember);
      margin: 0 0 10px;
    }
    .sp-swatches { display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 12px; }
    .sp-swatches span {
      display: inline-grid; place-items: center;
      min-width: 56px; height: 34px;
      padding: 0 8px;
      border-radius: 3px;
      background: var(--s);
      color: oklch(from var(--s) clamp(0, (0.6 - l) * 99, 1) 0 0);
      font-family: var(--sp-mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
